---
import Prose from './primitives/Prose.astro';

// Principles: exactly one next action, explicit owner, WIP max 5, queue max 3,
// no orphaned projects, proposal-only structural changes
---

<hr class="section-rule" aria-hidden="true" />

<section aria-labelledby="principles-title">
  <div class="section-header">
    <span class="section-number">04 /</span>
    <h2 id="principles-title" class="section-title">Principles</h2>
  </div>

  <Prose class="intro" measure={false}>
    The system enforces a small set of hard constraints. These are not suggestions — they are
    invariants that keep the operating system from degrading.
  </Prose>

  <ol class="principles-list">
    <li>
      <span class="principle-number">01</span>
      <span><strong>Exactly one next action.</strong> Every active project has a single primary next action. No ambiguity about what comes next.</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="principle-number">02</span>
      <span><strong>Explicit owner.</strong> Every project and every next action has a named owner — either a human or an AI agent. Shared responsibility is abdicated responsibility.</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="principle-number">03</span>
      <span><strong>WIP max 5.</strong> No more than five active projects at a time. Focus is enforced, not encouraged.</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="principle-number">04</span>
      <span><strong>Queue max 3.</strong> The waiting queue is capped at three items. If it overflows, prioritize or archive.</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="principle-number">05</span>
      <span><strong>No orphaned projects.</strong> Every project either has a next action or a decision record explaining why it is parked.</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="principle-number">06</span>
      <span><strong>Proposal-only changes.</strong> Structural changes (adding a bucket, changing a constraint, altering a feedback rule) require a written proposal and review. No ad-lib changes to the system.</span>
    </li>
  </ol>
</section>

<style>
  .intro {
    max-inline-size: var(--measure-legacy-wide);
    margin-block-end: var(--space-6);
  }
</style>
